  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.3Creatio Service\nOn this page\nLeverage the power of Creatio.ai to drastically improve your performance and automate mundane tasks in service-related activities. You can use plain language in the form of chat conversations to do the following:\n* summarize case\n* suggest case resolution\n* analyze case performance\n* check open cases\nYou can run these actions from any page, but we recommend running them from the page that provides context.\nCreatio.ai responds to your requests using **AI Agents** , separate entities tailored for the best performance in a particular area of Creatio. Creatio.ai chooses an agent automatically based on your request, but you can invoke a specific agent using the \"@\" character in your prompt if needed.\nFig. 1 Use Creatio.ai\n![Fig.\u00a01 Use Creatio.ai](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Service_Tools/creatio-ai/scr_case_resolution_agent.png)\nTo use Creatio.ai:\n1. **Open** the relevant section and record. For example, case.\n2. **Click** the ![btn_ai.png](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Service_Tools/creatio-ai/btn_ai.png) in the top right. This opens the Creatio.ai chat.\n3. **Enter** your request in the chat in plain language. For example, \"Suggest case resolution.\"\n**As a result** , Creatio.ai will start processing your request. It might ask you for confirmation or further information where appropriate.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Creatio.ai overview](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2528)\n[Creatio.ai architecture](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2548)",
